Model1: \[ \begin{aligned} LDI_i & \sim N(\mu_i, \sigma) \\ \mu_i & = \eta_i \\ \eta_i & = \beta_0 + \beta_1srh_i \end{aligned} \]

Prior1: \[ \begin{aligned} \beta_0 & \sim N(7, 3) \\ \beta_1 & \sim N(-.25, 3) \\ \sigma & \sim t^+_4(0,3) \end{aligned} \] Model2: \[ \begin{aligned} LDI_i & \sim N(\mu_i, \sigma) \\ \mu_i & = \eta_i \\ \eta_i & = \beta_0 + \beta_1comp_i \end{aligned} \] Prior2: \[ \begin{aligned} \beta_0 & \sim N(7, 3) \\ \beta_1 & \sim N(0, 4) \\ \sigma & \sim t^+_4(0,3) \end{aligned} \]

Model3: \[ \begin{aligned} LDI_i & \sim N(\mu_i, \sigma) \\ \mu_i & = \eta_i \\ \eta_i & = \beta_0 + \beta_1act_i \end{aligned} \] Prior3: \[ \begin{aligned} \beta_0 & \sim N(7, 3) \\ \beta_1 & \sim N(0, 4) \\ \sigma & \sim t^+_4(0,3) \end{aligned} \]
